<subSubSection id="F0B3FE610DF702DF818CA334CCD7A39F" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D146392341AE8CA15C322D7F8071D801" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC0662EAF1B84B5FC4CBB0DB93306B04" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
Molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation id="181E3956C580FACDEC4D04FB100C88A2" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 20" publicationUrl="10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" refId="B17" refString="Breure, ASH, Romero, PE, 2012. Support and surprises: molecular phylogeny of the land snail superfamily Orthalicoidea using a three-locus gene analysis with divergence time analysis and ancestral area reconstruction. Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde 141: 1 - 20, DOI: 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" title="Support and surprises: molecular phylogeny of the land snail superfamily Orthalicoidea using a three-locus gene analysis with divergence time analysis and ancestral area reconstruction." url="10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" volume="141" year="2012">Breure and Romero 2012</bibRefCitation>
, Breure unpublished data) strongly suggest that this genus, treated with several subgenera by 
<bibRefCitation id="7A20D4F6469B8675E14EBBA2920B3EEA" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, is polyphyletic and only the nominate taxon is grouping with 
<taxonomicName id="E793F59A28B0CA0E499A967C6D3CF67C" authorityName="Jay" authorityYear="1836" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteonidae" genus="Megaspira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megaspira" order="Heterostropha" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="554BB6EFFA33E8DA8A19560A4E49F87F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Megaspira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, further studies are needed as taxon sampling has been relatively low until now.
</paragraph>
